Package: gbtmkit
Title: Engine-Agnostic Pipeline for Group-Based Trajectory Modeling
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Shoji F.",
           family = "Nakayama",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "nies.sfn@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7772-0389"))
Description: A generic, reproducible pipeline for group-based trajectory
    modeling (GBTM) that follows the GRoLTS reporting checklist by
    construction. Model estimation is delegated to interchangeable backends
    (currently 'trajeR') behind a single interface, so binary and continuous
    outcomes are handled through one specification. The package provides
    algorithm and group-number selection, polynomial-shape search with GRoLTS
    fit diagnostics (entropy, average posterior probability, odds of correct
    classification, group sizes), and trajectory plotting.
